In England, in the seven days to 04 March, there were 198,155 new confirmed cases (350.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 February, there were 182,503 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 9% (15,652 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 09 March is 16,373,115 (28,953.3 cases per 100,000 population).
